    "experience": "2 questions were asked in OA of moderate difficulty. 1 was based on graphs (something to do with components of graph, \ncant remember the exact details) and the other was based on just logic. \n\nInterview round 1:  \nQ1) you are given a set of directed edges and vertices are from [0,n-1]. Also a set of locked vertices are given which \ncannot be entered or exited. Find the shortest path from a given source node to destination node. \nFollow question was-say you can now visit the locked nodes. Find the minimum number of locked nodes you have to visit \nin order reach destination from source. I solved them both using BFS and gave the time and space complexity. The \ninterviewer was satisfied and asked if I had any questions for him. I asked about work-life balance at Google and what \nkinda projects do interns work with. \n\nafter about half an hour I got the mail for Round 2 \n\nInterview round 2: \nYou are given 2 sets a=[x1,x2] and b=[y1,y2] where these 2 represent the set of all real numbers r1 and r2 such that \nx1<=r1<x2 and y1<=r2<y2. Find the set difference(i.e., a-b) and their intersection. I coded the solution and explained time \nand space complexity. The interviewer was satisfied and asked if I had any questions for him. I asked about the career \ntrajectory at Google and what will happen after the internship ends.",
