    "experience": "Note of warning: WF most likely came to the campus with a mass hiring intent beforehand, so the interview \nprocess was a lot more easier. They wanted ML/AI people this time around, which implies that DSA was not \ngiven much priority. \nRound 1: OA : Break up: DSA question, with 1 Leetcode medium. English, \"Business Analytics\" but well thats just \na name, it mostly had chill mental ability questions, they told everything you needed to know to solve it, but pls \nsolve quick. Another 2 DSA questions, Leettcode easy, 45 mins time. \nRound2: Online Interview: Focus on Resume, mostly basic stuff and cross questioning. If you have web dev \nprojects, be prepared to write pseudocode for that. Just a basic DSA question, had to write bubble sort :D Try to \nthink outside the box in dev questions, think of the different ways you can implement your skills in the given \nproblem. \nRound3: Offline Interview: Interviewer got very interested about my AI experience, asked me lots of basics like \nattention and transformer architecture. The interviewer really wanted to ask about Computer Networks, was \nabsolutely devasted and heartbroken that we hadn't studied it yet. He asked me to write Djikstra, wrote halfway \nand he declared \"woudn't work\" even though I was 100% sure that I was doing it correctly, from the min-heap \nand stuff. Was thinking of proving that it would indeed work, but I noticed he didn't seem to give a crap about \nwhether I could write it or not. Asked me what a min-heap was and asked me TC of inserting a node in a \nbalanced binary tree (bruh, didn't even ask me to rebalance the tree). Then it looked like he couldn't take it any \nmore and asked me a Networks problem. Thankfully it was just naming the 7 layers in the OSI model. Asked me \na couple of Resume oriented problems. \nRound 4: HR: Mostly formality, just chitchat, asked me a couple of questions about whether I knew about wells \nfargo. Asked me about my Hobbies, family background and so on. Everyone who went to HR was selected \n(whee).",
